Sentencas: Highly efficient utilization of low calorific value fuels is a major challenge for the current economic society.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As an electrochemical device, solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) offer an efficient approach, but the performance is limited by the concentration loss.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Hence, a dendritic fuel microchannels for dilute ethanol-fueled SOFCs is designed by phase inversion technique to accelerate the mass transport and improve the conversion efficiency in this study.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on the three-dimensional X-ray computed tomography technology, the porosity of the obtained dendritic microchannels is around 40%, and the absolutely permeability is 0.31 mu m(2), which can guarantee the efficient fuel transport.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Benefiting from the dendritic microchannels, the electrochemical performance increases from 363.1 mW cm(-2) to 713.8 mW cm(-2) at 750 C using 10% ethanol as fuel, and the concentration loss can be negligible.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the fuel utilization of dendritic microchannels increase from 34.6% to 97% by reducing the ethanol concentration from 30% to 10% at 0.3 V.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The corresponding maximum power density only decrease 7% at 750 C (677.1 mW cm(-2) vs 632.7 mW cm(-2)).
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All the results demonstrate that the design of dendritic microchannels for SOFCs is an efficient solution to accelerate the gas diffusion and improve the conversion efficiency of the low calorific value fuels.
Titulo: Highly efficient and stable fuel-catalyzed dendritic microchannels for dilute ethanol fueled solid oxide fuel cells
